 - paper title: Comparisons of characteristics of magnetic clouds and cloud-like structures during 1995-2012
 - abstract: Using eighteen years (1995 – 2012) of solar wind plasma and magnetic field data (observed by the Wind spacecraft), solar activity (e.g. sunspot number: SSN), and the geomagnetic-activity index (Dst), we have identified 168 magnetic clouds (MCs) and 197 magnetic-cloud-like structures (MCLs), and we have made relevant comparisons. The following features are found during seven different periods (TP: total period during 1995 – 2012, P1 and P2: first and second half-period during 1995 – 2003 and 2004 – 2012, Q1 and Q2: quiet periods during 1995 – 1997 and 2007 – 2009, A1 and A2: active periods during 1998 – 2006 and 2010 – 2012). (1) During the total period, the yearly occurrence frequency is 9.3 for MCs and 10.9 for MCLs. (2) In the quiet periods 〈N
